Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance of a random local search configurator for tuning the neighbourhood size parameter of an algorithm for two different function classes. This falls under the domain of algorithm configuration and optimization, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses statistical analysis and machine learning techniques to evaluate the performance of the configurator, which are common in the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithmic performance, which is a topic in the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the cutoff time on the performance of the configurator, which is a topic in the subfield of software engineering (cs.SE).
